This version contains updates that can help you manage your handwriting. Get easier access to colors with the handwriting color picker. Select a handwriting and tap the color palette to change the color of the handwriting. The smallest pen is now thinner making it easier to write small print. The highlighters are now thicker so you can highlight your notes more easily. The beautification of handwriting has been improved for several languages including German Spanish and Dutch. More bug fixes and improvements!

More new features to help you structure your ideas! Lists: Add text lists directly on the canvas. Note grids: Organize your notes with a note grid. New templates: Understand your customers better with the new templates for empathy cards and persona creation. Bug fixes: In addition to general bug fixes we ve fixed two major bugs that prevented some users from editing text or sharing boards. Stacks: We have removed the ability to create new object stacks based on user feedback. We are working on finding new ways to group content on a board in the near future.

This version includes updates that make organizing ideas and structuring meetings much easier Templates: Now in public trial. You can insert collaboration templates on the canvas for brainstorming sprint planning and more. Lots of bug fixes including several improvements to help for the disabled.

Improved selection and grouping logic to make the selected content easier to see and understand
Object snapping: Adjust the canvas so that it can be easily adjusted when you move it around with the object snapping option enabled.
We ve added support for over 40 languages making it easier to express and share ideas in your preferred language.

This release contains bug fixes and improvements

Our latest release has several exciting new features: Toolbar Docking: You can change your toolbar location to left right or bottom using the settings menu. Tool Tips: Press and hold on buttons in the toolbar or context menus to see a description of their functionality. Accessibility Checker: There s a full refresh of the accessibility checker which should make it much easier to ensure that your content is understandable for everyone.

We ve added rotation snapping on all items so it should be much easier to align your work and to scale and rotate items independently. We ve also improved keyboard navigation by making the new side panels used throughout the app accessibility landmarks.
Bug fixes
EDU customers can now use education themed stickers to collect poll responses and give feedback in real time
Settings and its sub menus are now in a full height side panel providing a more consistent user experience across devices features and platforms!
Bug fixes and general polish to improve your Whiteboard experience

We have a lot of exciting improvements in this release: Meeting Invite: Your meetings now appear as suggested contacts so you can invite all participants with a single tap Selections: Selection visual enhancements make it much more obvious what content is selected Highlighter Colors: New highlighter color and thickness options help you emphasize your points Education: Education customers will also see the send to OneNote menus in an easy to use side panel

Sign in with a Work or School account to use Ink Beautification a new Intelligence feature activated by the context menu wand button that transforms any handwritten notes into more legible ink strokes. Also in this update: Un synced changes are now called out more clearly in the board picker to make sure you don t lose your work. There s an improved accessibility experience when sending a Whiteboard to OneNote.

We ve redesigned the people picker! It s now easier to find and invite contacts to a board or share your board using a web link. We also had a big focus on fixing bugs over the last several weeks so we hope you enjoy a more stable usable and accessible experience with this update.

The board picker has a whole new look! It s now easier to find boards you ve been invited to join as board titles last modified dates and collaboration status are all more visible. We ve addressed a bug that occasionally caused a loading issue at start up for certain devices. Plus there are several animation improvements and bug fixes throughout the app.

Your most recently selected colors are now applied to newly created text and sticky notes so that you only have to set your preferred colors once Find the content you want to be working on more quickly with improved board ordering in the board picker Presence bubbles make it easier to understand the edits of remote participants

We hear you! Lots of highly anticipated changes with this release Customize your ink color and thickness with new pen colors and thickness levels. Change your board background color and gridline pattern. Includes the option for a black background to reduce eye strain. Type text directly on your board to let those without pen or touch contribute more easily. Usability performance and bug fixes. Plus check out this new preview features if you log in with an EDU account on iPad: Send whiteboards directly to your OneNote Class Notebooks for safe keeping. Have any suggestions We re all ears. Send us your feedback through our in app support Whiteboard Settings Send Feedback
Bug fixes and performance improvements

Lot s of new Whiteboard goodness in this release. Smash that UPDATE button to: Lock any image to the whiteboard background and never worry about accidentally erasing moving or having to recreate template like content again. Make sure your whiteboard is easy for people of all abilities to read and edit with a new Accessibility Checker. Access improved sticky note editing experience. Just double tap to add text let your ideas flow fast. Your recognized shapes and tables now have a hand drawn effect applied to them to help you impress your peers with your penmanship. When opening a whiteboard we now show you a fancy loading animation to help pass the time and so you don t sit wondering if anything is happening . A sprinkling of usability performance and bug fixes to make your whiteboarding experience a bit more polished.
